          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "**Haida** (X̱aad Kíl) — a language isolate of Haida Gwaii, British Columbia. The 2010 atlas marks it *critically endangered*: fewer than 50 fluent speakers, nearly all elders. Two dialects, Massett and Skidegate, each with its own orthography.",
